        "paragraph_index": 1,
        "text": "### Chemistry context\n\nAspirin (2-acetoxybenzoic acid) is catalogued in SRD-46 but was never critically evaluated — it carries the class **\"Ligands not selected\"** and has zero measurements with any metal. This is chemically reasonable: aspirin hydrolyses rapidly in aqueous solution to **salicylate** (2-hydroxybenzoate) and **acetate**, so equilibrium studies with intact acetylsalicylate are rare. Any Pu(IV)–carboxylate complexation work in the literature would more typically involve the hydrolysis products.",
